FIG. 6 is a block diagram of a clock counter shown in FIG. 4;


FIG. 7 is a circuit diagram of the RAS generating circuit and the internal interleave generating circuit shown in FIG. 4;


FIG. 8 is a timing chart of a data read operation of the memory shown in FIG. 4 performed when the burst length is equal to 4;


FIG. 9 is a timing chart of a data read operation of the memory shown in FIG. 4 performed when the burst length is equal to 8;


FIGS. 10A, 10B, 10C, 10D, 10E and 10F are respectively diagrams showing methods of setting the burst length in the semiconductor memory,


FIG. 11 is a block diagram of a parallel-to-serial converter circuit shown in FIG. 4;


FIG. 12 is a table showing a status of each switch shown in FIG. 11 with respect to a case in which the burst length is 1, 2 or 4;


FIG. 13 is a timing chart showing operations of first and second registers shown in FIG. 11:


FIG. 14 is a timing chart showing operations of a 4-bit-to-2-bit-conversion circuit and a latch&level-shifter circuit shown in FIG. 11 when the burst length is 4;


FIGS. 15A and 15B are tables showing operation conditions of four control-clock signals psclk0z-psclk3z and two output-control-clock signals outp0z and outp1z with respect to cases in which the burst length is 1, 2 and 4.


FIG. 16A is a circuit diagram of any one of delayed flip-flops DFF shown in FIG. 11;


FIG. 16B is a timing chart showing operations of the configuration of FIG. 16A;


FIG. 17A is a circuit diagram of any one of the output buffers shown in FIG. 11;


FIG. 17B is a timing chart showing operations of the configuration of FIG. 17A; and


FIG. 18 is a circuit diagram showing a configuration of the latch&level-shifter circuit shown in FIG. 11;


FIG. 19 is a block diagram of a second embodiment of the present invention; and


